PiperOrigin-RevId: 410815661
Change-Id: I93039ae0ac3f884b51a03ce23ade5b28c9d377c5","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/d14127861789523187080a24b77c35322f074f2f"},{"sha":"939f707660e5782cc7cdc7299fb50f6427199a15","author":{"email":"7da1985d121fd79537822bb42be62798d2d2aa23@google.com","name":"Prakalp Srivastava"},"message":"Add optional attributes to specify operand/result layouts in mhlo::CustomCallOp.

A custom call can also have layout constrains on operands and results which can be specified as optional `operand_layouts` and `result_layouts` attributes. The layout attribute is an array of rank-1 index tensors and the i-th layout attribute specifies the layout for i-th operand/result.

The `operand_layouts` & `result_layouts` attributes can be specified under the following constraints checked in the verifier:
1) Either both `operand_layouts` and `result_layouts` are specified or none.
2) None of the operands are of tuple type.
3) None of the results are of tuple type except the common case of single tuple result packing non-tuple values is allowed. In this case the i-th `result_layouts` attribute specifies the layout of i-th element in the result tuple.

[{"sha":"4cb9a07e96ef039ef1074d76cecc7043020b1b80","author":{"email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org","name":"A. Unique TensorFlower"},"message":"Fix XLA on cuDNN pre-8.1: missed a place that needed to fall back to legacy.

Since cuDNN didn't (sufficiently) support the frontend APIs as used by XLA
until 8.1, attempting to use it on older versions was an error.  A recent
change flipped the default of an XLA flag to enable cuDNN frontend, and this
was honoured regardless of the current cuDNN version.  Since the recent API
changes were carefully made to allow switching seamlessly between the two, we
can just second-guess that flag when cuDNN frontend is unavailable, and use
legacy APIs anyway.
